        <title>AI Specialisation</title>
        <author>
            <name>Erico Leonardo Alexander Pizarro Gutierrez</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://newmaddog.github.io/ai-specialisation.html"/>
        <id>https://newmaddog.github.io/ai-specialisation.html</id>
        <media:content url="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Skaermbild-2024-04-09-205152.png" medium="image" />

        <updated>2024-04-09T20:52:40+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Skaermbild-2024-04-09-205152.png" alt="" />
                    What type of AI? In my Specialization, I have created a squad&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Skaermbild-2024-04-09-205152.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <h1 class="align-center">What type of AI?</h1>
<p> </p>
<p>In my Specialization, I have created a squad that works together to win against the player. There are four types of AI: Medic, Leader, Decoy, and Flanker, each with their own role to play.</p>
<h1 class="align-center"><strong>Behavior Trees</strong></h1>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Behavior-tree.png" alt="" width="267" height="333" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Behavior-tree-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Behavior-tree-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Behavior-tree-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Behavior-tree-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<p>I have chosen behavior trees as the decision-making system among the three available approaches (behavior trees, decision trees, and state machines). My preference for behavior trees stems from the greater control they offer in determining how the AI agent prioritizes its decisions. Furthermore, behavior trees enhance flexibility in the decision-making process by accommodating both ordered and selected decision-making scenarios.</p>
<table class="align-center" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 560px; height: 350px;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td style="width: 100%; height: 50%;"><figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Leader.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Leader-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Leader-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Leader-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Leader-lg.png 1024w"></figure></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;"><strong>Leader</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;">The Leader holds the team together</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table class="align-center" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 560px; height: 350px;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td style="width: 100%;" scope="colgroup"><figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Medic.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Medic-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Medic-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Medic-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Medic-lg.png 1024w"></figure></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;"><strong>Medic</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;">The Medic focuses on keeping his teammates alive</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/MedicHeal.gif" alt="" width="600" height="349"></figure>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/MedicCondition-4.png" alt="" width="720" height="498" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/MedicCondition-4-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/MedicCondition-4-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/MedicCondition-4-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/MedicCondition-4-lg.png 1024w"></figure><br>The Medic AI will scan the battlefield to locate any teammate, whether the Decoy or the Leader, with less than 35% of their maximum health remaining. Once a wounded ally is detected, the Medic will move to their position and administer the necessary medical care to restore their combat readiness.</p>
<table class=" align-center" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 560px; height: 350px; border-style: none;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td style="width: 100%;"><figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Decoy.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Decoy-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Decoy-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Decoy-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Decoy-lg.png 1024w"></figure></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;"><strong>Decoy</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%;">The Decoy distracts and diverts the player's attention</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/DecoyDefend.gif" alt="" width="600" height="349"></figure><br>The decoy roll is to help the teammate with taking damage and also shoot a lot.<br>Decoy takes players attention so the Flanker can go around wtihout the player notice it.<br>The decoy also helps the medic, if the medic has below 50% health it will begin shooting twice the speed.</p>
<p> </p>
<table class="align-center" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 560px; height: 350px; border-style: none;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 76px;">
<td style="width: 100%; height: 76px;"><figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/Flanker.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Flanker-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Flanker-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Flanker-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/responsive/Flanker-lg.png 1024w"></figure></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 50.3594px;">
<td class="align-center" style="width: 100%; height: 50.3594px;"><strong>Flanker</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 107.953px;">
<td style="width: 100%; height: 107.953px;">The Flanker sneaks behind the player to attack from behind</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/AIFlanker.gif" alt="" width="600" height="349"></figure>
<p>The Flanker role is to flank the player while remaining undetected. It will move behind cover, using stealth and evasion to approach the target from an unexpected angle. The goal is to surprise and outmaneuver the target.<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/9/FlankerHealing.gif" alt="" width="600" height="349"></figure>
<p>Unlike the Decoy and Leader AI agents, the Flanker will not receive direct healing support from the Medic. Instead, the Flanker AI has been designed with a self-preservation protocol - when its health drops below 35%, it will automatically move to the nearest available cover and begin administering self-healing.</p>
<p>This design choice was inspired by the stealth mechanic from game call Metal Gear Solid 3, where the player must rely on their own resourcefulness and ability to find safe locations to recover when injured, rather than depending on a dedicated medic. The Flanker AI embodies this same principle, prioritizing mobility and self-sufficiency over team-based healing.</p>
            ]]>
        </content>
    </entry>
    <entry>
        <title>Project 8 : Power To The Valley</title>
        <author>
            <name>Erico Leonardo Alexander Pizarro Gutierrez</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://newmaddog.github.io/project.html"/>
        <id>https://newmaddog.github.io/project.html</id>
        <media:content url="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-28-145306.png" medium="image" />

        <updated>2024-04-09T19:07:58+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-28-145306.png" alt="" />
                    Summary The game concept draws from Pacific Drive, centering on vehicular exploration&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-28-145306.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <h2 id="summary" class="align-center">Summary</h2>
<p>The game concept draws from Pacific Drive, centering on vehicular exploration in an expansive world. Players navigate the environment in their adaptable car, encountering a knowledgeable mechanic early in their journey. This mechanic serves as a guide, introducing the player to the game's progression system. The mechanic explains how gathering scrap and other resources scattered throughout the landscape is crucial for advancement. These materials are essential for upgrading the player's vehicle, allowing access to new, previously restricted areas. The gameplay loop integrates exploration, resource collection, and vehicle enhancement, creating a compelling experience that motivates players to uncover the world's mysteries and progress through the story.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center" ><figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/HighresScreenshot00010-5.png" alt="" width="1920" height="997" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/HighresScreenshot00010-5-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/HighresScreenshot00010-5-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/HighresScreenshot00010-5-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/HighresScreenshot00010-5-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<figcaption ></figcaption>
</figure>
<h1 class="align-center">Details</h1>
<p>For this project, we chose to use Unreal Engine 5 with AngelScript. As programmers, we were relatively new to this engine, so we took our time learning it while simultaneously familiarizing ourselves with AngelScript.</p>
<h2 id="contribution" class="align-center">Contribution</h2>
<h3 class="align-center">PostMaster</h3>
<figure class="post__image post__image--full"><img  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150415.png" alt="" width="1440" height="674" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150415-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150415-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150415-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150415-lg.png 1024w"></figure><figure class="post__image post__image--right"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150425.png" alt="" width="213" height="267" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150425-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150425-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150425-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150425-lg.png 1024w"></figure>One of my collaborations involved creating PostMaster in Unreal Engine 5 using AngelScript. The approach I took was to create an empty actor called ActorPostMaster. Within this actor, I also created a component named PostMasterComponent. This component maintained a list of all actors that had an EventComponent. With these three elements in place, we could implement events where, if something happened, we could call an actor to react to its specific event.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150442.png" alt="" width="1719" height="358" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150442-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150442-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150442-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150442-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<p>This section demonstrates the implementation of the PostMaster system and the process of registering EventComponents with the PostMasterComponent. As shown in the image.<br><br><br></p>
<h3 class="align-center">NPC</h3>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150143.png" alt="" width="794" height="244" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150143-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150143-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150143-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150143-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150127-2.png" alt="" width="498" height="449" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150127-2-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150127-2-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150127-2-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150127-2-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<p>I also implemented NPC to the game, combining UE5 and AngelScript. I use UE5 to create path points for the NPC to walk to. I use the settings in UE5 to visualize their locations, and since these path points are local, I transform them to world positions within the AngelScript.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150206.png" alt="" width="468" height="302" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150206-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150206-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150206-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150206-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150246.png" alt="" width="684" height="243" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150246-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150246-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150246-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150246-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150255-2.png" alt="" width="427" height="242" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150255-2-xs.png 300w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150255-2-sm.png 480w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150255-2-md.png 768w ,https://newmaddog.github.io/media/posts/8/responsive/Skaermbild-2024-07-29-150255-2-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<p>We also implemented animations for the NPCs. I set it up so that a specific animation plays depending on the NPC's position. This allows the designer to choose which animation plays in each location. So, when the NPC finishes walking, it plays the animation that was chosen.</p>
            ]]>
